Gemini said
Actually, it's the opposite.

In the old pip world, setup.py develop was deprecated in favor of pip install -e .. In the modern Pixi/Conda world, --editable (or pixi dev) is the standard way to develop local tools.

The Brief Reality:
Is it deprecated? No. pixi global install --editable is a first-class feature designed specifically for your use case.

Why use it? It creates a symlink to your source code. Without it, Pixi copies your files into a hidden environment. If you edit hello.py without --editable, your command won't change until you reinstall.

Future-proof? Yes. It follows PEP 660, the modern Python standard for editable installs.

The "Pixi 2026" way:
If you want to be ultra-modern, Pixi is moving toward pixi dev workflows, but for Global CLI tools (stuff you want to run from any folder), pixi global install --path . --editable remains the cleanest way to keep your scripts live and syncable.

Bottom line: Use it. It’s the "Live Reload" for your terminal tools.

