Run this once from ~/scripts/mytools. The --editable flag ensures that any change you make to the .py files is reflected instantly when you run the command.

Bash
pixi global install --path . --editable
5. Why this is the "Endgame" Setup
Expandability: Want a new command? Add a new .py file in src/mytools/, add one line to [project.scripts], and Pixi handles the rest.

Zero Friction: You don't need to be in the folder. You don't need to type pixi run. Just type hello.

Cleanliness: All your dependencies are isolated in a hidden Pixi environment, but the binary is available globally at ~/.pixi/bin/hello.

Note: Ensure ~/.pixi/bin is in your $PATH. If hello doesn't work immediately, add export PATH="$HOME/.pixi/bin:$PATH" to your .zshrc or .bashrc.





